{{italic title}}
The '''''Complete UK Hit Singles''''' is a book that lists every [[Single (music)|single]] to have made it into the [[UK Singles Chart]] since its inception in 1952. As well as providing chart data on each of the hits, the book also provides a brief biography on each hit maker, together with facts and trivia about each hit, such as whether it qualified for a BPI sales award, was featured in a film or contains a sample of another track. The book was written by Graham Betts and is the companion volume to '''''Complete UK Hit Albums'''''. <!--"It will have the first number #1 single ever recorded to the latest single." Huh?-->

==See also==
*[[List of number-one singles (UK)]]

{{DEFAULTSORT:Complete UK Hit Singles 1952-2006}}
[[Category:Books about pop music]]


{{ref-book-stub}}

{{Orphan|date=March 2017}}
The '''Declaration of Independence of The Negro Peoples of The World''' was drafted and adopted at the [[Universal Negro Improvement Association and African Communities League#First international convention|first international convention]] of the [[Universal Negro Improvement Association and African Communities League]] held in New York, 1920, over which [[Marcus Garvey]] presided as Chairman, and at which he was elected Provisional President of Africa.
