__NOTOC__ {{italic title}} [[File:1914 Toulouse Guide Joanne cover.png|thumb|140px|right|Cover of guide to Toulouse, 1914]] [[File:1912 map Guides Joanne.jpg|thumb|right|Map of geographic regions covered in the ''Guides Joanne'' series, 1912]] '''''Guides Joanne''''' (est.1841) was a series of French-language travel [[guide book|guide books]] to Europe founded by [[Adolphe Joanne]] and published in Paris. Routes followed the railways at first,<ref name="Harp2001">{{cite book|author=Stephen L. Harp |title= Marketing Michelin: Advertising and Cultural Identity in Twentieth-Century France |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=IcB2x74UgUAC|year= 2001|publisher=Johns Hopkins University Press|isbn=978-0-8018-6651-7}}</ref> and later volumes guided readers by province.{{sfn|Nordman|1997}}
