| {{flag|India}}
| Asia
| {{dts|-5000}}
| {{dts|1947|Aug|15}}
| data-sort-value="Britain/United Kingdom"|{{flag|United Kingdom}}
| India's local name [[Bhārat Gaṇarājya|Bhārat]] derives from the legendary Bharata (either [[Bharata (Mahabharata)|Dushyanta's son Bharata]] or [[Bharata Chakravartin|Rishabha's son Bharata]]), held by tradition as the first emperor to unite India in 5000 BC.{{cn|date=August 2018}} Modern Indian subcontinent was united by Mahajanapadas in 600 BC. Political unity in verified historiography was first achieved by [[Chandragupta Maurya]]'s founding of the [[Mauryan Empire]] in 322 BC, followed by the [[Gupta Empire]] of 320 AD and [[Maratha Empire]] in 1674 before era of the [[Mughals]] and then [[British Raj]] from 1857 to Independence in 1947.
