| {{flag|Israel}}
| Asia
| {{dts|-1300}}
| {{dts|1948|May|14}}
| data-sort-value="Britain/United Kingdom"|{{flag|United Kingdom}}
| The 12 tribes conquer the holy land under the leadership of Joshua, then Israel goes through "The period of the [[Biblical judges|judges]]" leading to the [[Kingdom of Israel (united monarchy)|Kingdom of Israel]] unified under King [[Saul]], c. 1020 BC, divided into separate kingdoms of Israel and Judea, which fall to [[Neo-Assyrian Empire|Neo-Assyrian]] and [[Neo-Babylonian Empire|Neo-Babylonian]] empires in 722 and 586 BC, respectively. In the 2nd century BC, Judea re-gains independence as [[Hasmonean]] kingdom after revolt against the Hellenist [[Seleucid Empire]]. Conquered by [[Pompey]] of the [[Roman Empire]] in 63 BC, and subsequently falls to [[Byzantine Empire|Byzantine]], [[Umayyad Caliphate|Umayyad]], [[Abbasid Caliphate|Abbasid]], [[Crusader states|Crusader]], [[Mamluk]], [[Ottoman Empire|Ottoman Turkish]], and [[British Empire|British]] rule, before regaining independence as the [[State of Israel]] in 1948.
