| 1986–present: '''Fifth Philippine Republic''' <br />  1981–1986: [[Fourth Philippine Republic]] <br /> 1973 - 1981: [[Philippines under Marcos|Philippines in the Martial Law]] <br />  1946–1972: [[Third Philippine Republic]]  <br /> 1942–1943: A puppet state of the [[Japanese Empire]] ([[Second Philippine Republic]]). <br /> 1898–1942, 1943–1946: Part of the United States <br /> 1535–1898: A colony of Spain <br /> Pre-1535: The Philippine Islands had a numerous sinified states, Indianized kingdoms and Muslim states. In [[Luzon]], there were the Ivatan people, the Society of Cordillera, the Kingdoms of Pangasinan and Ma-i, Kota Selurong and the [[Tondo Dynasty]]. The Confederation of the Madyas and the Rajahnate of Cebu were in [[Visayas]]. Lastly, in [[Mindanao]], there were the [[Sultanate of Maguindanao]], Butuan Rajahnate and the [[Sultanate of Sulu]]. The [[Bruneian Empire]] occupied [[Palawan|Palawan_(island)]] and parts of Mindanao too.
