{{Infobox recurring event | name = White Privilege Conference | native_name = | native_name_lang = English | logo = | logo_alt = | logo_caption = | logo_size = | image = | image_size = | alt = | caption = | status = Active | genre = [[White privilege]], [[anti-racism]], [[ethnic group|ethnic]] | date = <!-- {{start date|YYYY|mm|dd}} "dates=" also works, but do not use both --> | begins = <!-- {{start date|YYYY|mm|dd}} --> | ends = <!-- {{start date|YYYY|mm|dd}} --> | frequency = Annually | venue = | location = | coordinates = <!-- {{coord|LAT|LON|type:event|display=inline,title}} --> | country = [[United States]] | years_active = <!-- {{age|YYYY|mm|dd}} Date of the first occurrence --> | first = 2000 | founder_name = Eddie Moore Jr. | last = <!-- Date of most recent event; if the event will not be held again, use {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD|df=y}} --> | prev = | next = | participants = | attendance = | capacity = | area = | budget = | activity = | leader_name = | patron = | organised = <!-- "organized=" also works --> | filing = | people = | member = | sponsor = <!-- | or sponsors = --> | website = {{URL|http://whiteprivilegeconference.com/}} | footnotes = }}
The '''''White Privilege Conference''''' is a yearly conference held to discuss the issue of [[white privilege]].<ref name=EN>{{cite web|title=Thousands of teachers flock to ‘White Privilege Conference’|date=April 15, 2016|first=Victor|last=Skinner|url=http://eagnews.org/thousands-of-teachers-descend-on-white-privilege-conference/|publisher=[[Education Action Group Foundation]]}}</ref><ref name=NYT>{{cite web|title=At New York Private Schools, Challenging White Privilege From the Inside|first=Kyle|last=Spencer|date=February 20, 2015|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/02/22/nyregion/at-new-york-private-schools-challenging-white-privilege-from-the-inside.html?_r=0|work=[[The New York Times]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nyym.org/?q=Spark-January2016-Hitchcock|title=The White Privilege Conference|date=January 28, 2016|first=Jeffrey|last=Hitchcock|publisher=[[New York Yearly Meeting]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite episode|title=Tim Wise - Between Barack and a Hard Place: Racism and White Denial in the Age of Obama|url=http://www.c-span.org/video/?285738-1/book-discussion-barack-hard-place|accessdate=April 5, 2015|series=[[Book TV]]|credits=[[Tim Wise]]|network=[[C-SPAN]]|station=White Privilege Conference|location=Memphis|airdate=April 4, 2009}}</ref>
The conference features several workshops and groups for students and adults about racism, race, perceived white privilege, [[sexism]], black [[oppression]], [[racial injustice]], as well as discussions of [[LGBT|lesbian, gay and transgender rights]], as well as [[Islam]] and [[Islamophobia]].<ref name=EN/>
==History and founding== The White Privilege Conference was founded in 2000 by Eddie Moore Jr., a former diversity director at Brooklyn Friends.<ref name=NYT/>
As of 2016, many New York private schools had students and faculty attending the conference.<ref name=NYT/>
==2016 White Privilege Conference deemed "too white"== At the 2016 White Privilege Conference attendees complained that the conference was "too white".<ref name=TDC>{{cite web|title=White Privilege Conference Attendees Complain Conference Is Too White|author=Neff, Blake|date=April 18, 2016|url=http://dailycaller.com/2016/04/18/white-privilege-conference-attendees-complain-conference-is-too-white/|publisher=[[The Daily Caller]]}}</ref> Inspired by the 2015 [[Twitter]] [[88th Academy Awards|#OscarsSoWhite]] campaign, Twitter users adopted the hashtag #WPCSoWhite and claimed the conference that was supposed to fight [[white privilege]] instead entrenched it.<ref name=TDC/>
The Twitter tag appeared to have been started by Aeriel Ashlee, an [[Asian Americans|Asian American]] education consultant who attended the 2016 conference and objected to many sections of a keynote address delivered by [[white people|white]] historian [[James W. Loewen]], including his use of the [[Nigger|N-word]].<ref name=TDC/>
==Media criticism== The conference has been criticized by some in the media<ref name=NB>{{cite web|url=http://newsbusters.org/blogs/kristine-marsh/2015/02/20/nyt-applauds-elite-ny-private-schools-white-privilege-propaganda|publisher=[[NewsBusters]]|title=NYT Applauds Elite NY Private Schools’ ‘White Privilege’ Propaganda|first=Kristine|last=Marsh|date=February 20, 2015}}</ref> as nothing more than [[white guilt]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Always room in the budget for white guilt|first=Katherine|last=Kersten|date=April 13, 2011|url=http://www.startribune.com/always-room-in-the-budget-for-white-guilt/119508364/|work=[[Star Tribune]]}}</ref>
